<slide title="Compress">
<blurb>
HTTP supports native compression by using Lempel-Ziv encoding 
(LZ77).  Its the same encoding mechanism used by the popular 
unix tool &lt;code>gzip&lt;/code>. 
</blurb>
<list title="Compression Advantages">
<bullet slide="1">Greatly reduces bandwidth</bullet>
<bullet slide="1">Cross browser compliant</bullet>
<bullet slide="1">Compression can cache as well</bullet>
</list>

<list title="Compression Disadvantages">
<bullet slide="1">CPU intensive on the Server</bullet>
<bullet slide="1">CPU intensive on the Client</bullet>
</list>
</slide>